result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Korey M Adams in court with attorney David R. Dickmann.  Michael Daniel Zell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Officer Jacob Guse is sworn and questioned by Attorney Zell.  Testifies to having contact with the defendant outside of Big Al's Bar.  Witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom.  Testifies that he noticed that the defendant was drinking and he was aware that defendant was under an absolute sobriety condition.  Cross-examination by Attorney Dickmann.  

Court finds probable cause to believe that a felony was committed and that the defendant committed it. Bond is continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 28, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Korey M Adams in court.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Bond reinstated. Court finds good cause to go outside time limits for preliminary hearing.
